===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|Chinese mythology}} the [[w:Zhenniao|zhen]] (a hawk-like, snake-eating [[bird]] with poisonous feathers, which is based on {{taxfmt|Pitohui|genus}} spp. or {{taxfmt|Spilornis cheela|species}})
#* {{zh-x|吾 令 鴆 為{wéi} 媒 兮，鴆 告 余 以 不好。|I bade the '''''zhen''-bird''' to be my go-between; the '''''zhen''-bird''' told me: "Not good!"|ref=Chuci}}
#* {{zh-x|又 東北 百-二十 里，曰 ^女-几 之 山，…… 其 鳥 多 白-鷮{jiāo}，多 翟{dí}，多 鴆。|120-li more northeastwards, [there's a place] called Mount Nüji; [...] as for the birds, there are many white ''jiāo''-pheasants, many ''dí''-pheasants, and many '''''zhèn''-hawks'''.|ref=Shanhaijing}}
# [[poisonous]]
#* {{zh-x|太后 怒，乃 令 人 酌 兩 卮 鴆酒 置 前，令 ^齊-王 為{wéi}壽。|The {{w|Empress Lü|Empress Dowager}} was so angry as to order her servants to pour two goblets of '''poisonous / poisoned''' liquor in front, letting the {{w|Liu Fei, Prince of Qi|King of Qi}} drink for her longevity. |ref=Hanshu}}
# to [[poison]]
#* {{zh-x|溫 之 會，^晉-人 執 ^衛 ^成-公 歸 之 于 ^周，使 醫 鴆 之，不 死，醫 亦 不 誅。|At the assembly at Wen, the men of {{w|Jin (state)|Jin}} held Duke Cheng of {{w|Wey (state)|Wey}} captive and returned him to {{w|Zhou dynasty|Zhou}}. They dispatched a physician to '''poison''' him but failed to kill, and also the physician was not executed.|ref=Guoyu}}
# poison
#* {{zh-x|公 田，^驪-姬 受福，乃 置 鴆 于 酒，置 堇 于 肉。|The {{w|Duke Xian of Jin|Duke}} went out hunting; {{w|Li Ji (concubine)|Li Ji}} accepted the blessings. Then she put '''poison''' in the liquor and put aconite in the meats.|ref=Guoyu}}

